[Guest]: There's this Pedro Almodovar film, I don't know whether you've seen it, called The Law

02:14:03.480 --> 02:14:04.840
[Guest]: of Desire.

02:14:04.840 --> 02:14:08.720
[Guest]: So I want that to be the title of my book, The Law of Desire.

02:14:08.720 --> 02:14:14.920
[Guest]: And I just want to look at three or four different sexual activities and the laws governing them

02:14:14.920 --> 02:14:17.920
[Guest]: and to think about what that says about us and our society.

02:14:17.920 --> 02:14:23.120
[Guest]: So I want to think about marriage, I want to think about prostitution, I want to think

02:14:23.120 --> 02:14:29.100
[Guest]: about adultery, I want to think about transgender, and of course, homosexuality.

02:14:29.100 --> 02:14:33.600
[Guest]: And think about, I mean, these are just the five right now, rape might be one of them,

02:14:33.600 --> 02:14:35.520
[Guest]: one might come out, one might go in.

02:14:35.520 --> 02:14:42.200
[Guest]: But just to think about how we imagine these sexual crimes, and how we imagine the law

02:14:42.200 --> 02:14:45.040
[Guest]: can actually put a lid on them.

02:14:45.040 --> 02:14:46.400
[Guest]: Just to think about those.

02:14:46.400 --> 02:14:52.440
